---
export const prerender = true;

import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Case Study: Combat Waffle Studios - XR Awards 2025"
  description="How Combat Waffle Studios Mastered the XR Awards - A detailed case study on winning strategies for XR Game of the Year."
>
  <Header />
  
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-white">
    <!-- Case Study Header -->
    <section class="relative bg-[#0E1022] pt-32 md:pt-40 pb-20 md:pb-32 overflow-hidden">
      <!-- Decorative Background Rings -->
      <!-- Left Ring -->
      <div class="absolute -left-20 md:left-0 top-1/4 -translate-y-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[300px] h-[300px] md:w-[450px] md:h-[450px]">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 rounded-full" style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, #E91E8C 0%, #5D1635 100%);"></div>
        <div class="absolute top-[55px] left-[55px] right-[55px] bottom-[55px] md:top-[75px] md:left-[75px] md:right-[75px] md:bottom-[75px] rounded-full bg-[#0E1022]"></div>
      </div>
      <!-- Right Ring -->
      <div class="absolute -right-20 md:right-0 top-3/4 -translate-y-1/2 translate-x-1/2 w-[300px] h-[300px] md:w-[450px] md:h-[450px]">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 rounded-full" style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, #00D4D8 0%, #0A4B52 100%);"></div>
        <div class="absolute top-[55px] left-[55px] right-[55px] bottom-[55px] md:top-[75px] md:left-[75px] md:right-[75px] md:bottom-[75px] rounded-full bg-[#0E1022]"></div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="relative z-10 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <h1 class="page-title text-white mb-6">
          Unlocking Success: How Combat Waffle Studios Mastered the XR Awards
        </h1>
        
        <!-- Decorative Dots -->
        <div class="flex justify-center gap-2 mb-6">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
        </div>
        
        <p class="page-subtitle text-white">
          Detailed Case Study | 9 min read
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Case Study Content -->
    <section class="py-16" style="background-color: #F2F2F2;">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm p-8 md:p-12">
          
          <!-- Introduction -->
          <p>Today, we're diving deep into the winning strategies of Combat Waffle Studios, exploring exactly how their game 'Ghost of Tabor' achieved acclaim at the XR Awards.</p>
          
          <p><strong>This isn't just a general overview…</strong></p>
          
          <p>We're offering a detailed, step-by-step breakdown, straight from our exclusive interview with CEO Scott Albright.</p>
          
          <p><strong>In fact:</strong></p>
          
          <p>This guide is based on the very strategies that resulted in 'Ghost of Tabor' becoming an award-winning title.</p>
          
          <p>If you're seeking <strong>actionable insights</strong> AND <strong>real-world examples</strong>, you'll find this case study invaluable.</p>
          
          <p>Let's go.</p>
          
          <!-- Section 1 -->
          <h2>Discovering the Winning Formula: Combat Waffle Studios' Nomination Strategy</h2>
          
          <p>Combat Waffle Studios' path to the XR Awards with 'Ghost of Tabor' was marked by a thoughtful, community-driven strategy.</p>
          
          <p>As Scott Albright, CEO, recalls…</p>
          
          <!-- Quote Callout -->
          <div class="quote-callout">
            <div class="quote-icon">"</div>
            <p class="quote-text">We were actually motivated by the community to enter… the community just kept saying 'VR Game of the Year'; 'You need to enter'."</p>
            <p class="quote-attribution">— Scott Albright, CEO Combat Waffle Studios</p>
          </div>
          
          <p>This genuine push from their audience laid the foundation for their nomination, emphasising the significance of community engagement in their success.</p>
          
          <p>But how?</p>
          
          <h3>Key Elements of Their Strategy:</h3>
          
          <!-- Numbered List with Styled Numbers -->
          <div class="numbered-list">
            <div class="numbered-item">
              <div class="number-badge">1</div>
              <div class="numbered-content">
                <h4>Community-Driven Motivation</h4>
                <p>The encouragement from their players was a pivotal motivator.</p>
                <p>"It was something that wasn't really on our radar because we were so heavy into development, but the community just kept saying 'You need to enter'."</p>
                <p>This support highlighted the game's impact and resonance with its audience.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="numbered-item">
              <div class="number-badge">2</div>
              <div class="numbered-content">
                <h4>Emphasising Unique Features</h4>
                <p>'Ghost of Tabor' was distinguished by its innovative gameplay and narrative depth.</p>
                <p>The studio focused on showcasing these elements, understanding that a standout game needs more than just technical prowess—it needs a story and character.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="numbered-item">
              <div class="number-badge">3</div>
              <div class="numbered-content">
                <h4>Narrative and Emotional Connection</h4>
                <p>The nomination highlighted not just the game but the passion and journey behind it.</p>
                <p>Albright's approach was about creating a narrative that connected with the judges and the wider XR community.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <p>As Combat Waffle Studios demonstrated, a strategic approach, rooted in community support and a compelling narrative, can pave the way for success at the XR Awards.</p>
          
          <!-- Takeaway Box -->
          <div class="studio-advice-box">
            <h3>Takeaway for Studios:</h3>
            <p>Your nomination is a reflection of your game's story and its impact on the community.</p>
            <p>Albright's advice echoes this sentiment: "Just having your name as somebody like 'These guys had the chance' should be more than enough motivation for anybody to enter."</p>
            <p>A well-crafted nomination should not only highlight the game's strengths but also its connection with the audience and the journey behind its creation.</p>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Section 2 -->
          <h2>Evaluating the Return on Investment</h2>
          
          <p>Combat Waffle Studios' experience with 'Ghost of Tabor' at the XR Awards is a perfect case study to understand the cost-benefit dynamics of participating in such a prestigious event.</p>
          
          <p>Scott Albright's perspective offers a real-world view of the tangible and intangible returns on this investment.</p>
          
          <h3>Breaking Down the Costs:</h3>
          
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Nomination Fee:</strong> There is an inherent monetary cost in nominating a game.</li>
            <li><strong>Resource Allocation:</strong> The preparation for a compelling nomination demands both time and resources.</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Weighing Against the Benefits:</h3>
          
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Increased Visibility and Industry Recognition:</strong> Albright notes, "Being a finalist is one thing… but when you're a winner, everyone flocks to you."</li>
            <li><strong>Networking and Industry Connections:</strong> "Executives at Sony and other places… have now reached out and connected."</li>
            <li><strong>Boost in Team Morale:</strong> Winning had a profound effect on the team's morale.</li>
          </ul>
          
          <!-- Advice Box -->
          <div class="studio-advice-box">
            <h3>Advice for Studios:</h3>
            <p>Winning an XR award is as much about the journey as it is about the final product. Studios aiming for success in such competitive awards need to focus on:</p>
            
            <!-- Numbered List -->
            <div class="numbered-list-simple">
              <div class="numbered-item-simple">
                <div class="number-badge">1</div>
                <div class="numbered-content-simple">Continuous improvement</div>
              </div>
              <div class="numbered-item-simple">
                <div class="number-badge">2</div>
                <div class="numbered-content-simple">Genuine community engagement</div>
              </div>
              <div class="numbered-item-simple">
                <div class="number-badge">3</div>
                <div class="numbered-content-simple">Resourceful use of their platforms</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <p>As Combat Waffle Studios demonstrated, a committed, player-centric approach can lead to extraordinary success, even for indie studios with limited mainstream support.</p>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Final Quote -->
          <div class="quote-callout">
            <div class="quote-icon">"</div>
            <p class="quote-text">Everyone flocks to you at that point because now you're an award-winning studio.</p>
            <p class="quote-attribution">— Scott Albright, CEO Combat Waffle Studios</p>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Conclusion -->
          <h2>Your Next Steps</h2>
          
          <p>Combat Waffle Studios' story is not just a tale of victory; it's a blueprint for achieving recognition in the XR Awards.</p>
          
          <p>Which strategy from today's insights are you going to implement first? Will it be harnessing the power of community feedback, focusing on a unique game feature, or maybe leveraging the award for broader industry connections?</p>
          
          <p><strong>Finally, this is your call to action: don't just contemplate; act.</strong></p>
          
          <p>If you believe your studio has what it takes, step forward and nominate your project for the XR Awards.</p>
          
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-title {
    font-size: 35px;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .page-title {
      font-size: 45px;
    }
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
  }

  .prose {
    color: #374151;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: #111827;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .prose h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #111827;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .prose h4 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: #111827;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .prose ul,
  .prose ol {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .prose li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .prose ul {
    list-style-type: disc;
  }
  
  .prose ol {
    list-style-type: decimal;
  }
  
  .prose strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #111827;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  /* Quote Callout Design */
  .quote-callout {
    position: relative;
    background: #FFFFFF;
    border: 1px solid #00D4D8;
    padding: 2rem 2.5rem 1.5rem 2.5rem;
    margin: 3rem 0;
    border-radius: 0;
  }
  
  .quote-icon {
    position: absolute;
    top: 1rem;
    left: -0.5rem;
    font-size: 6rem;
    line-height: 1;
    color: #00D4D8;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: normal;
    background: white;
    padding: 0.25rem 0;
  }
  
  .quote-text {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-style: normal;
    color: #1F2937;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    margin-left: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .quote-attribution {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #6B7280;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    text-align: right;
    font-style: normal;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  /* Studio Advice/Takeaway Box Design */
  .studio-advice-box {
    background: #FFF9E6;
    border: 2px solid #FFD54F;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
  }
  
  .studio-advice-box h3 {
    color: #F57C00;
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #FFD54F;
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .studio-advice-box p {
    color: #5D4037;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .studio-advice-box p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  
  /* Numbered List with Badges */
  .numbered-list {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }
  
  .numbered-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  
  .number-badge {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667EEA 0%, #764BA2 100%);
    color: white;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.3);
  }
  
  .numbered-content {
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .numbered-content h4 {
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .numbered-content p {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  .numbered-content p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  
  /* Simple Numbered List (for inside boxes) */
  .numbered-list-simple {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  
  .numbered-item-simple {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  
  .numbered-item-simple .number-badge {
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  
  .numbered-content-simple {
    flex: 1;
    color: #5D4037;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  }
  
  /* Responsive adjustments */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .numbered-item {
      gap: 1rem;
    }
    
    .number-badge {
      width: 40px;
      height: 40px;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
    
    .quote-callout {
      padding: 1.75rem 1.5rem 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    }
    
    .quote-icon {
      font-size: 4.5rem;
      left: -0.4rem;
      top: 0.75rem;
    }
    
    .studio-advice-box {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>

